# Code Summarization using LLMs
This repository contains the implementation of our paper [Code Summarization using Large Language Models](https://arxiv.org/abs/2307.08623). We present a novel approach to summarize code snippets by leveraging large language models (LLMs), such as GPT-3, to generate natural language descriptions of the code's functionality and purpose. By providing the model with a high-quality dataset consisting of paired examples of code and corresponding summaries, we train the LLM to understand the relationship between code and textual descriptions. 

## Dataset Preprocessing
We use the [CodeSearchNet](https://github.com/github/CodeSearchNet) dataset for training and evaluation. To preprocess the data, run `python preprocess_data.py`. This script extracts the Java code from the raw JSON files and stores them in separate `.java` files. It also generates the corresponding summaries by extracting the function name and docstring comments from the source code.

## Model Training
To train the LLM, we employ the OpenAI API to fine-tune the `text-davinci-003` model on our custom dataset. You can find the details about the training process in the `train_model.py` file.

## Inference
Once trained, the model can be used for inference by providing it with a code snippet and generating a summary description. For instance, consider the following code snippet:

